contentrichtext.text: '''Ext''', '''ext''' or '''EXT''' may refer to: * [[Ext functor]], used in the mathematical field of homological algebra * [[Extended file system]], a file system created for Linux; see also [[ext2]], [[ext3]] and [[ext4]] * [[Ext (JavaScript library)]], a programming library used to build interactive web applications * [[Exeter International Airport]] (IATA airport code), in Devon, England * [[Extratropical cyclone]], a mid-latitude cyclone * [[Extremaduran language]] (ISO language code), spoken in Spain * [[Extremeroller]], a former roller coaster at Worlds of Fun, Kansas City, Missouri * [[Cadillac Escalade EXT]], a pickup truck * [[Extension_(telephone)|Extension]], a number appended to the end of a telephone number, or used internally. * [[Example (disambiguation)|Example]], a short hand use for example. {{disambig}}
